<p><a href="https://twitter.com/pauldambra/status/916712725060947974">…made a toot-storm</a> about using construction as a metaphor for software engineering.</p>

<blockquote>
  <p>I've never really got on with construction metaphors for software. The cost of mistakes and rework is high in construction</p>
</blockquote>

<p><img src="/images/toot.jpeg" alt="the toot itself" /></p>

<p>This isn't saying that Software isn't putting things together but rather I've seen people justify not 'being agile' by using construction metaphors.</p>

